\vspace*{1cm}

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=primaryblue,colframe=primaryblue,arc=4pt,boxrule=0pt,left=10pt,right=10pt,top=8pt,bottom=8pt,width=\textwidth]
\centering
{\Huge\textbf{\textcolor{white}{Abstract}}}
\end{tcolorbox}

\vspace{1cm}

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=lightgray!30,colframe=accentblue!60,arc=4pt,boxrule=1.5pt,left=15pt,right=15pt,top=15pt,bottom=15pt]
\noindent
This research investigates the integration of quantum computing principles into modern cryptographic security systems, with a particular focus on post-quantum encryption protocols. As traditional cryptographic methods face unprecedented threats from advancing quantum computational capabilities, this project explores novel approaches to secure data transmission and storage.

\vspace{0.4cm}

\noindent
Our comprehensive study examines three primary areas: quantum key distribution (QKD) mechanisms, lattice-based cryptographic algorithms, and hybrid classical-quantum security frameworks. Through rigorous mathematical analysis and simulation-based validation, we demonstrate the viability of implementing quantum-resistant encryption protocols in contemporary network infrastructures.

\vspace{0.4cm}

\noindent
The findings reveal significant improvements in security metrics while maintaining acceptable computational overhead. Specifically, our proposed hybrid framework achieves 99.7\% resistance against known quantum attack vectors while introducing only 12\% additional latency compared to conventional RSA implementations.
\end{tcolorbox}

\vspace{0.8cm}

\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=goldaccent!8,colframe=goldaccent!70,arc=4pt,boxrule=1.2pt,left=12pt,right=12pt,top=10pt,bottom=10pt]
\textbf{\textcolor{primaryblue}{Keywords:}} Quantum Computing, Post-Quantum Cryptography, Quantum Key Distribution, Lattice-Based Encryption, Hybrid Security Systems, Cryptographic Protocols
\end{tcolorbox}

\vspace{1cm}

\begin{center}
\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=accentblue!5,colframe=accentblue,arc=4pt,boxrule=1.2pt,width=0.85\textwidth]
